### Buffer solution

Buffer solution:
- #Definition A solution in which the pH does not change significantly when small amounts of acids or alkalis are added
- Keep the pH of the substance constant from addition of small amount of acid or base
- Consist of weak acid + conjugate base or weak base + conjugate acid
- #Concept Example: 
$$
\begin{gather}
\text{Acid base reaction: } CH_{3}COOH (aq) \rightleftharpoons H^{+} (aq) \ + CH_{3}COO^{-} (aq) \\
\text{Buffer solution: } CH_{3}COONa(s) + aq \rightarrow
 CH_{3}COO^{-} (aq) \ + Na^{+} (aq)
\end{gather}
$$

|                When H+ is added                |                    When OH- is added                     |
|:----------------------------------------------:|:--------------------------------------------------------:|
| $CH_{3}COO^{-} + H^{+} \rightarrow CH_{3}COOH$ | $CH_{3}COOH + OH^{-} \rightarrow CH_{3}COO^{-} + H_{2}O$ |
| Equilibrium shift left | Equilibrium shift right |
| Large reserve supply of $CH_3COOH$ and $CH_{3}COO^{-}$ results in negligible change of $[CH_3COOH]$ and $[CH_{3}COO^{-}]$ | < |

- #Calculation Calculation:
$$
\begin{gather}
HA \; \rightleftharpoons \; H^{+} + A^{-} \qquad MA \; \rightarrow \; M^{+} + A^{-} 
\\
K_{a} = \frac{[H^{+}][A^{-}]}{[HA]} \\
pK_{a} = - log_{10} {\frac{[H^{+}][A^{-}]}{[HA]}} \\
pH = pK_{a} \: + \: log_{10} \frac{\text{[conjugate base]}}{\text{[acid]}}
\end{gather}
$$
